IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF NEAR NORTH HEALTH SERVICE CORPORATION (NNHSC) IS TO PROVIDE ACCESS TO HIGH QUALITY HEALTH CARE TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH, WELL-BEING, AND SAFETY OF THE DIVERSE POPULATIONS AND COMMUNITIES WE SERVE. WE ARE A CULTURALLY SENSITIVE AND CULTURALLY COMPETENT, PATIENT CENTERED COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER THAT EMPOWERS INDIVIDUALS THROUGH EDUCATION, DISEASE PREVENTION, AND PROMOTING HEALTHY BEHAVIORS, REGARDLESS OF ONE'S INABILITY TO PAY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC). IN ADDITION, NNHSC QUALIFIES FOR THE CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTION DEDUCTION UNDER SECTION 170(B)(1)(A) AND HAS BEEN CLASSIFIED AS AN ORGANIZATION THAT IS NOT A PRIVATE FOUNDATION. THE ORGANIZATION DETERMINED THAT IT WAS NOT REQUIRED TO RECORD A LIABILITY RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE IS AN INTERNAL REVIEW PROCESS WHICH IS PERFORMED BY THE DIRECTOR OF FINANCE AND THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR. SUBSEQUENT TO THAT REVIEW, THE 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD, WHO THEN SUBMITS THE RETURN TO THE ENTIRE BOARD FOR APPROVAL. A COPY OF THE RETURN IS KEPT ON RECORD FOR PUBLIC REVIEW SHOULD THERE BE SUCH A REQUEST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL STAFF AND BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENT EVERY YEAR, WHICH IS KEPT IN EACH STAFF AND BOARD MEMBER FILE. DISCLOSURE OF CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY QUESTION IS PRESENTED TO EVERY STAFF OR BOARD MEMBER DURING THE RECRUITING OR HIRING PROCESS. FURTHERMORE, AT ANY JUNCTURE WHEN MAJOR DECISIONS ARE ABOUT TO BE MADE, INDIVIDUALS ARE ASKED TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS THAT MAY EXIST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMPENSATION FOR STAFF IS BASED ON THE RESULTS OF ANNUAL REVIEWS CONDUCTED BY THE HEALTHCARE TRADE ASSOCIATIONS. THE SURVEY IS USED AS A GUIDE IN DETERMINING THE CORPOARATION'S SALARY SCHEDULE IN COMPARISON TO ITS INDUSTRY.
